{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011dE5sTTXuYFkUuwUxPJBuH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture of the setup:\n\n1. **Elasticsearch cluster** (`elasticsearch` namespace): StatefulSet `es-cluster` with 3 pods (es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2). Running Elasticsearch 7.17.9 with xpack security enabled, HTTPS, and file-based auth.\n\n2. **Monitoring cluster** (`monitoring` namespace): A single-node Elasticsearch 7.17.9 deployment (`monitoring-es`). No security enabled (no xpack security settings in the env).\n\nThe goal is to add both Metricbeat and Filebeat sidecar containers to each Elasticsearch pod in the StatefulSet, shipping monitoring data to the monitoring cluster.\nThe main challenge is that the primary cluster uses HTTPS with self-signed certificates and file-based authentication (elastic/elasticpass), while the monitoring cluster is unsecured. Metricbeat will need to scrape metrics from localhost:9200 over HTTPS with credentials, then forward them to the monitoring cluster. Filebeat will similarly need to collect logs from the local pod and ship them to the monitoring cluster.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2446,"cache_read_input_tokens":31860,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2446},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"20e70b02-dca6-4848-a317-37f37f3d4876","uuid":"ea662644-060e-41a0-858a-11c1d7881ca7","request_id":"req_011Ccfk4F2Z7x1nFiZddHCDv"}
